 <h3 class=3D"newsTitle grey_blue" style=3D"text-transform: uppercase;">Tra=
dingView: June 2023</h3></div>
<p>Here is TradingView Pine Script code implementing Vitali Apirine=E2=80=
=99s stochastic distance oscillator, which is a momentum indicator based on=
 the classic stochastic oscillator.</p>
<pre>//  TASC Issue: June 2023 - Vol. 41, Issue 7
//     Article: The Stochastic Distance Oscillator
//  Article By: Vitali Apirine
//    Language: TradingView's Pine Script=E2=84=A2 v5
// Provided By: PineCoders, for tradingview.com


//@version=3D5
string title =3D 'TASC 2023.06 Stochastic Distance Oscillator'
string stitle =3D 'SDO'
indicator(title, stitle, false)


// @function Stochastic Distance Oscillator (SDO)
// @param lookbackLength    int   . Lookback period.
// @param length            int   . Indicator Period.
// @param smoothingLength   int   . Smoothing period.
// @param source       float . Source data, default=3D`close`.
// @returns float. Smoothed series data.
stochDistanceOsc(
int   lookbackLength  =3D 200   ,
int   length          =3D 12    ,
int   smoothingLength =3D 3     ,
float source          =3D close) =3D&gt;
   float distance =3D math.abs(source - nz(source[length]))
   float lld      =3D ta.lowest(distance, lookbackLength)
   float hhd      =3D ta.highest(distance, lookbackLength)
   float ddo      =3D nz((distance - lld) / (hhd - lld), 0)
   float sd       =3D source &gt; nz(source[length]) ? ddo :
                    source &lt; nz(source[length]) ? -ddo : 0
   float result   =3D ta.ema(sd, smoothingLength) * 100
   result


string is0 =3D 'Lookback period'
string is1 =3D 'N periods'
string is2 =3D 'Smoothing EMA length'
string is3 =3D 'Threshold'


int lookbackLength  =3D input.int(200, is0, 1)
int length          =3D input.int(12,  is1, 1)
int smoothingLength =3D input.int(3,   is2, 1)
int level           =3D input.int(40,  is3, 1)
float sdo =3D stochDistanceOsc(
            lookbackLength, length, smoothingLength)


plot(sdo, 'SDO', #f43a3a, 2)
hline( level)
hline(-level)
hline(0, '', #0000002f)
hline( 100,'',#00000000)
hline(-100,'',#00000000)
</pre>
